# Forge holds no model provider key of its own for chat — users bring their own
# credentials through the in-app Providers panel, and each is stored in an
# httpOnly cookie, never in the environment:
#   - a Hugging Face token for cloud chat
#   - an OpenAI-compatible connection for chat against your own provider
#   - an OpenAI-compatible connection for codegen (the AI that writes playgrounds)
#
# The ONE optional server-side key is the free codegen "taste" below. It's off by
# default: a cloned Forge without it is strictly bring-your-own.

# Optional. A Groq API key used to write a first-time visitor's FIRST playground
# for free — the "taste" of the product before they bring their own codegen key.
# Each browser gets exactly ONE free generation (tracked by an httpOnly cookie);
# everything after — regenerate, modify, new playgrounds — needs their own key.
# Get one at https://console.groq.com/keys
GROQ_API_KEY=

# Set to 1 to actually turn the free tier on. GROQ_API_KEY alone does nothing.
#
# IMPORTANT: /api/codegen has no authentication. The one-per-browser cookie stops
# honest re-use, but a determined abuser can clear cookies to pull more free
# generations. Your real cost ceiling is a SPENDING CAP set on the Groq account
# itself — set one before enabling this on a public deploy. Left unset, every
# user brings their own codegen provider.
FORGE_FREE_CODEGEN=
